- Two key European congresses fall in launch window (UEG Week in 8 weeks, ECCO Congress in 5 months)

**Internal pressure:**
- Marketing wants MSLs to "support sales conversations" — this is a compliance line you cannot cross. MSLs are non-promotional.
- Sales head: "We need MSLs in the room with KOLs alongside our reps." (Also a compliance issue.)
- Market Access wants real-world data published quickly to support reimbursement negotiations
- Regulatory has flagged that any messaging deviating from the EMA label is a serious issue
- Compliance head: "Don''t repeat the mistakes from the 2022 launch" — referring to a prior product where MSL boundaries got blurry and resulted in an internal investigation

**Specific requests landing on your desk:**
1. A prominent IBD KOL (Dr. Hartung, Berlin) wants Cynara to fund a 200-patient real-world study — €380k commitment, 18 months
2. A community gastroenterologist asks if you can "explain the data" at his hospital''s monthly internal meeting — borderline territory between education and promotion
